            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> **Disorganized layout** – landing page, sponsors and news sections lack clear hierarchy\n\nthe main page could use some layout improvements but your current mock looks like a big regression. why in the world would we occupy the entire \"above the fold\" area with 90% empty space and smaller buttons?\n\nthis makes me suspect we're not going to make progress here.\n\n> * **Poor project structure** - lots of stuff in the root, flat file organizatio\n\nnot sure what you mean. in general, \"flat\" is structure is far superior to over-nested, over-granular structure where people think they are doing something useful but actually just forced everyone to poke around in their meaningless categories.\n\n> * **Visual inconsistency** - poorly adjusted and meaningless spacing\n\nspacing of headings, block-level elements, etc., could definitely be improved. but your mock screenshot looks literally 5x, maybe 10x worse.\n\n> Component-based architecture with suitable file structure\n\nidk, maybe. if it involves a complex framework beyond some \"layouts\" then no thanks. It should be as close to vanilla markdown as possible. Because these static site generators are a dime a dozen and we'll need to migrate again sooner or later.",
